        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 7:32PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 732 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
White Pigeon, or 12 miles south of Three Rivers, moving east at 35
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Sturgis, Three Rivers, Middlebury, Constantine, White Pigeon,
Centreville, Colon, Nottawa, Scott, Fawn River, Mottville, Leonidas,
Mendon, Burr Oak, Shipshewana, Klinger Lake, Fairfax, Howe, Wasepi,
and Findley.

This includes Interstate 80 in Indiana between mile markers 101 and
125.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight EDT for
north central and northeastern Indiana...and southwestern Michigan.</instruction>
